g.text: Sequence diagram for executing builds on Buildbot
initiated by a /buildbot comment in Github Pull Request
The semantics are not defined so
I just picked a simple string
Feedback to Github User: "We've received your message and begin processing shortly"
We'll be using it to store state updates to the build.
Feedback to Github User: "A check was created for you"
Show check run on PR page
We send properties to buildbot (e.g. CheckRunID, PullRequestID, etc.) that it sends back to the app
later with the HTTPStatusPush service. From these properties we can deduce which check we have to update.
Feedback to Github User: "A build has started" (First time the URL to buildbot is provided)
add build state to existing summary
adjust run state according to build result
Also update the build log comment
add build state to existing summary
adjust run state according to build result
Also update the build log comment
